{% block content %}
  <section>
    <div class="section-label accent-border">
      <h2 class="section-title">Our mission</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card accent-border">
      <p>
        Our mission is to provide inclusive spaces for the NZ software community to connect and grow together.
      </p>
      <p>
        When we said <em>spaces</em>, we’re not just talking about an annual volunteer run event. 
      </p>
      <p>
        We have big dreams beyond the annual flagship NZ Tech Rally conference. We want to run in a sustainable way which includes ongoing community building, paying people for their time, helping people get paid for their content/class/workshops, and etc.
      </p>
      <p>
        But this year, we’re bootstrapping; starting from zero. We will have to rely on different types of volunteers who are interested in our cause until we can get off the ground.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-label section-label--header accent-border">
      <h2 class="section-title">What to expect as a one-day &amp; longer term volunteer</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label accent-border">
      <h3 class="section-title">Perks</h3>
    </div>

    <div class="card accent-border">
      <p>For the time being, these are our volunteer perks: </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Our eternal gratitude</li>
        <li>Free entry to events you're involved in</li>
        <li>Experience managing ticketed events</li>
        <li>Experience managing and growing a software community</li>
        <li>A natural way of networking with industry experts, supporters, mentors, and top talents</li>
        <li>A chance to be a part of our longer-term vision and really know what we’re doing to get NZ Tech Rally there</li>
        <li>LinkedIn or other type of work reference; should you want one.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section-label accent-border">
      <h3 class="section-title">Disadvantages</h3>
    </div>

    <div class="card accent-border">
      <p>If those sound cool to you, we feel it’s only right to disclose things that are less-cool. </p>
      <ul>
        <li>You will not get to watch all the talks live or enjoy an event the way paying participants can. But don't worry, our talks are recorded.</li>
        <li>You will have to get up really early on the day of the event, as we need help with setup and pack down.</li>
        <li>When we say time commitment, we really mean it. We’ve estimated that these are the amount of time you need to put in to ensure the event’s success.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

